   42 - Fixed dotcl/dotcl#49: every generated class file's top-level <type> constant is now emitted via cl:define-symbol-macro instead of cl:defconstant (emit-type-constants-and-clos-registration, apg-class-file-generator.lisp). defconstant's init-form runs at load time; when a generated package is included as an ASDF :depends-on dependency (rather than spliced directly into the consuming root system's own :components, the workaround documented in the issue), the consumer's build process loads the dependency's fasl -- running dotnet:resolve-type there -- before the target assembly is necessarily in the build process's own type-resolution context, so resolution fails even though the identical call succeeds once the deployed app actually runs. A define-symbol-macro only registers a substitution: resolve-type now runs solely where <type> is actually USED, deferring it to the deployed app's real runtime. This is free of any repeated-evaluation cost after first use: DotCL.Runtime >= 0.1.17 (already this generator's minimum, per Version 41) memoizes a resolve-type miss's eager AppContext.BaseDirectory assembly-load-and-retry runtime-side after first expansion. The immediately adjacent CLOS type-registration eval-when (which calls dotnet:static \"DotCL.Runtime\" \"EnsureDotNetTypeClass\" (dotnet:resolve-type ...)) is narrowed from (:compile-toplevel :load-toplevel :execute) to (:load-toplevel :execute) for the identical reason -- :compile-toplevel unconditionally forced its own resolve-type call during the dependency's compile phase, which would reintroduce the exact same failure even after <type> itself was fixed. See doc/generator-design-notes.md's Version 42 section and doc/package-generator-dependencies.md.
