rsion 43 section.
   44 - Added --ensure-type/--no-ensure-type (sticky, applying directly to the current and every subsequent --class -- OFF by default, unlike this file's other sticky flags, none of which apply until an explicit --enable-*/--export-all-*/--output-all-* is given): gates whether generate-class-file emits the \"Register C# Type with CLOS\" eval-when (dotnet:static \"DotCL.Runtime\" \"EnsureDotNetTypeClass\" ...) that every previous version emitted unconditionally. Investigation into DotCL.Runtime's actual source (Runtime.CLOS.cs/Runtime.DotNet.cs/Runtime.Type.cs, dotcl/dotcl v0.1.17) found this eager call is not needed by anything this generator itself emits: class-of/typep on any wrapped .NET object, and dotnet:class-for-type (what --defgeneric's generated defmethods use, since Version 41), already lazily call EnsureDotNetTypeClass themselves on first real need. Its only remaining effect is on registration ORDER: when two .NET types share a simple name across different namespaces, whichever is registered first keeps the friendly dotcl-internal::|Name| CLOS class symbol; eager, generation-order-based registration made that outcome deterministic, whereas without it the winner depends on whichever type the running program happens to touch first. This only matters for hand-written user code dispatching via the simple-name pattern documented in this file's/doc/generator-design-notes.md's \".NET CLOS Integration\" section -- never for --defgeneric, which is immune (dispatches via class-for-type on the exact fully-qualified name), and, per dotcl/dotcl#50 (already in the required 0.1.17), a collision no longer causes silent cross-type misdispatch either way, only a less-friendly assembly-qualified name plus a printed warning for whichever type loses the race. emit-type-constants-and-clos-registration (apg-class-file-generator.lisp) gained a required ENSURE-TYPE parameter wrapping the eval-when emission in a cl:when; generate-class-file threads it through from the resolved-class plist's new :ensure-type key (make-resolved-class/resolve-batch-entry, apg-batch-discovery.lisp), which cascades to discovered classes exactly like :defgeneric/:extension-methods already do (never :constant-properties) per Version 39's flag-propagation rule. Program.cs's manifest carries the new per-class boolean, set from a new sticky ensureType default (mirroring exportAllParents/enableDefgenericStatic) rather than a matched --ensure-type/--no-ensure-type per-class override pair, since this flag has none -- a deliberate, requested exception to this file's usual two-tier sticky-default/per-class-override convention.
