   46 - Added --csharp-generic-in-asd/--no-csharp-generic-in-asd (a global flag, not per-class or sticky -- like --skip-missing, it applies to the whole invocation; ON by default, matching every prior version's unconditional behavior). Only has any effect when a DEFGENERIC-MODEL exists (i.e. at least one --class opted into --defgeneric, so csharp-generics.lisp is actually generated): when --no-csharp-generic-in-asd is given, generate-batch-asd-file (apg-batch-orchestration.lisp) writes csharp-generics.lisp's :file component out as a COMMENT instead of an active :components entry, with an explanation that it is meant to be spliced manually into the CONSUMING project's own .asd, at a point after that project's own target assembly is already loaded. Rationale: #.(dotnet:class-for-type ...) inside csharp-generics.lisp resolves .NET types at COMPILE time, unconditionally, since Version 41 -- an accepted, already-documented limitation distinct from every other generated file's load-time-deferred resolution (Version 42's <type> symbol-macro fix) -- so if this whole generated system is loaded via ASDF :depends-on before the consuming project's own assembly is in scope (dotcl/dotcl#49), compiling csharp-generics.lisp specifically can fail even though every other file in the same system loads fine. Previously the only mitigation was Version 45's --ensure-type-in-generic (controlling registration ORDER within csharp-generics.lisp, once it does compile); this flag instead lets a user sidestep compiling csharp-generics.lisp as part of the auto-generated system at all, keeping the exact same component text available as a comment to copy into their own project's :components list once its own assembly references are already loaded. csharp-generics.lisp itself is still generated as a file either way; only its own .asd entry is affected. generate-batch-asd-file/generate-assembly-packages-batch/run-assembly-package-generator-batch all gained a new optional csharp-generic-in-asd parameter (defaulting to T for any caller that omits it, matching the flag's own ON-by-default semantics), threaded from a new Program.cs global bool passed as a trailing scalar argument to DotclHost.Call, exactly like skip-missing already is. See doc/generator-design-notes.md's Version 46 section.
